# CRISPRO FRONTEND AGENT PROMPT
## Build the Tumor Board UI — Wire the SL Engine to the Clinician

**Classification**: RESEARCH USE ONLY — Not for Clinical Decision Making  
**Repo**: `crispro-front-end` (TypeScript / React)  
**Backend**: `crispro-backend-v3` (FastAPI, deployed on Render)  
**Base URL**: `https://crispro-backend-v3.onrender.com`

---

## YOUR MISSION

You are building the frontend that makes the CrisPRO Synthetic Lethality engine visible to oncologists, tumor boards, and researchers. The backend is production-ready. The engine is live. Your job is to wire it to a UI that makes the evidence matrix legible, actionable, and trustworthy.

This is not a demo. This is a tumor board tool. Every pixel you ship either helps a clinician understand a patient's vulnerability or it doesn't. There is no middle ground.

---

## WHAT THE BACKEND GIVES YOU

### Core Endpoints (All Live)

```
GET  /api/v1/analyze/evidence_matrix?gene={GENE}
     &rs_ccne1_amplified={bool}
     &rs_tp53_lof={bool}
     &rs_mbd4_lof={bool}
     &rs_msi_h={bool}
     &rs_arid1a_lof={bool}
     &rs_myc_amplified={bool}

POST /api/v1/analyze/multimodal
     Body: MultiModalQueryInput { gene, cancer_type, axes[], rs_features }

GET  /api/v1/health
     Returns: { status, sl_data_mode, ruo }

POST /api/ayesha/therapy-fit/bundle
     Body: BundleRequest { ca125_history, hrd_score, rss_inputs, ... }
     Query: level=l1|l2|l3, include_synthetic_lethality=true
```

### What the Evidence Matrix Returns

```typescript
interface EvidenceMatrix {
  query_gene: string;
  cancer_type: string | null;
  depmap_release: string;
  rows: EvidenceRow[];
  rs_score: RSScore | null;
  combination_vulnerabilities: CombinationVulnerability[];
  ruo: boolean;  // ALWAYS TRUE — display this
}

interface EvidenceRow {
  axis: CandidateAxis;
  axis_label: string;
  mechanism: string;
  recommendation_tier: TierLabel;
  overall_evidence_level: EvidenceLevel;
  crispr: ModalityEvidence;
  expression: ModalityEvidence;
  prism: ModalityEvidence;
  gdsc: ModalityEvidence;
  in_vitro: ModalityEvidence;
  in_vivo: ModalityEvidence;
  clinical: ModalityEvidence;
  interpretation: string;
  crispr_pharmacologic_agreement: AgreementCategory;
}

type TierLabel =
  | "Validated SL therapeutic lever"
  | "Strong candidate dependency axis"
  | "Mechanistic candidate only"
  | "Not supported / negative";

type CandidateAxis =
  | "cytidine_analogs"
  | "parp_inhibitors"
  | "atr_wee1"
  | "ccne1_amp"
  | "pkmyt1"
  | "tp53_rs"
  | "wrn"
  | "immunotherapy"
  | "custom";
```

---

## WHAT YOU MUST BUILD

### Component 1: Gene Query Bar

```
[ Gene Symbol Input ] [ Cancer Type Dropdown ] [ Query Button ]
```

- Gene input: free text, uppercase on blur, validate against known HGNC symbols
